{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 20,
  "title": "第二十章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "絕學無憂，唯之與阿，相去幾何？善之與惡，相去若何？人之所畏，不可不畏。"
    },
    {
      "text": "荒兮其未央哉﹗"
    },
    {
      "text": "眾人熙熙，如享太牢，如春登臺。"
    },
    {
      "text": "我獨泊兮其未兆，如嬰兒之未孩；"
    },
    {
      "text": "儽儽兮若無所歸。"
    },
    {
      "text": "眾人皆有餘，而我獨若遺。"
    },
    {
      "text": "我愚人之心也哉﹗"
    },
    {
      "text": "沌沌兮，"
    },
    {
      "text": "俗人昭昭，"
    },
    {
      "text": "我獨昏昏。俗人察察，"
    },
    {
      "text": "我獨悶悶。澹兮其若海，"
    },
    {
      "text": "飂兮若無止。"
    },
    {
      "text": "眾人皆有以，"
    },
    {
      "text": "而我獨頑似鄙。"
    },
    {
      "text": "我獨異於人，而貴食母。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 35
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "下篇，為學者日益，為道者日損。然則學求益所能，而進其智者也，若將無欲而足，何求於益。不知而中，何求於進。夫燕雀有匹，鳩鴿有仇，寒鄉之民，必知旃裘，自然已足，益之則憂。故續鳧之足，何異截鶴之脛，畏譽而進，何異畏刑。唯阿美惡，相去何若？故人之所畏，吾亦畏焉，未敢恃之以為用也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "歎與俗相返之遠也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "眾人迷於美進，惑於榮利，欲進心競，故熙熙如享太牢，如春登臺也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言我廓然無形之可名、無兆之可舉，如嬰兒之未能孩也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "若無所宅。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "眾人無不有懷有志，盈溢胸心，故曰，皆有餘也。我獨廓然無為無欲，若遺失之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "絕愚之人，心無所別析，意無所好欲，猶然其情不可覩我頹然若此也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所別析，不可為明。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "耀其光也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "分別別析也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 10,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "情不可覩。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 11,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所繫縶。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-13",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 12,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以，用也。皆欲有所施用也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-14",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 13,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無所欲為，悶悶昏昏，若無所識，故曰頑且鄙也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-15",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 14,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "食母，生之本也。人者皆棄生民之本，貴末飾之華，故曰我獨欲異於人。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
